The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Quippo to merge with Srei
                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      Quippo to merge with Srei
          OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT                          Hemant Kanoria in Calcutta on Thursday. Picture by Kishor Roy Chowdhury                                  
	Calcutta, Jan. 28: Srei Infrastructure Finance Company today said it would merge Quippo Infrastructure  its subsidiary engaged in the equipment rental business in telecom, oil and gas and construction  with itself.        
	The merger will be effective from April 1 and Quippo shareholders will get three Srei shares for every two of Quippo. The enterprise value of Quippo is, thus, pegged at 1.5 times that of Srei. All the five subsidiaries of Quippo will come under the Srei fold.        
	Srei shareholders will get four bonus shares for every five shares held.         
	Following the merger, Sreis net worth will be in excess of Rs 2,000 crore and this will give us a huge leverage to grow the companys business and balance sheet, Srei chairman Hemant Kanoria said.        
	Srei holds a 16.88 per cent stake in Quippo, while family members of the promoter group together own another 57 per cent.        
	Post-merger, promoters holding in Srei Infrastructure will go up to 46 per cent from 30 per cent now, Kanoria said.         
	Srei today reported a profit after tax of Rs 44.20 crore on a consolidated basis in the third quarter against Rs 8.77 crore a year ago.                                                                                                                                       
